The '''rare drop table''' or '''RDT''' is a drop table that is accessed by medium-level and high-level monsters. The rare drop table drops some rune items and other items of moderate value, and also has access to the [[gem drop table]] as a sub-table. The rare drop table also has a chance at rolling the mega-rare drop table.

The mega-rare drop table contains mostly empty drops, but also the rune spear, dragon spear and shield left half. The player does '''NOT''' need to have [[Legends' Quest]] completed to access the mega-rare drop table via the rare drop table, however it '''IS''' required to access it via the gem drop table.

Some monsters will have their rare drop table drops appear on an adjacent tile to the rest of the loot pile when the rare drop table is rolled. This can help the player distinguish if the drop came from the rare drop table or their standard drop table, if both tables share some of the same drops.

==Rare drop table==
At current prices, the expected value of a drop is approximately {{Coins|{{RDTValue}}}} when not wearing a ring of wealth.
